sample_extract_protocol_ch1: HS and healthy skin tissues were cut into small pieces and were digested with 2.5U/ml Dispase-II (Millipores Sigma, Cat#4942078001) in Hanks’ Balanced Salt Solution (HBSS, Corning, Cat#21-022-CM) overnight at 4°C. After digestion, the epidermis was peeled off and minced. The minced epidermis was incubated with 0.05% trypsin-EDTA at 37°C for 40 mins for further digestion. The suspension was then filtered through a 40um cell strainer and spun down at 300g at 4°C for 5 mins.  Cells were then subjec ...

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: HS and healthy skin tissues were cut into small pieces and were digested with 2.5U/ml Dispase-II (Millipores Sigma, Cat#4942078001) in Hanks’ Balanced Salt Solution (HBSS, Corning, Cat#21-022-CM) overnight at 4°C. After digestion, the epidermis was peeled off and minced. The minced epidermis was incubated with 0.05% trypsin-EDTA at 37°C for 40 mins for further digestion. The suspension was then filtered through a 40um cell strainer and spun down at 300g at 4°C for 5 mins. Collected single cells  ...
sample_data_processing: The demultiplexing, barcoded processing, cell multiplex oligo (CMO) processing, gene counting and aggregation were made using the Cell Ranger 'multi' software v6.0.2

sample_data_processing: FASTQ files were generated through BaseSpace using Illumina's bcl2fastq software., CUT-RUNTools-2.0 (https://github.com/fl-yu/CUT-RUNTools-2.0) was used to trim, align, and call peaks. Used default settings, EXCEPT set "frag_120" to "FALSE"., bigWig files were generated using deepTools bamCoverage version 3.5.1 with parameters -of bigwig --effectiveGenomeSize 2913022398 --normalizeUsing RPGC --ignoreForNormalization chrX chrM --binSize 10
